## Discoveries

- Bead metadata from `bd show noscope-3ez.9`:
  - Title: *Make validate command perform provider validation*
  - Description: Update `cmd_validate` to execute `provider::validate_provider` checks and emit actionable failures.
- Current `cmd_validate` behavior in `src/main.rs`:
  - Resolves provider via `client.resolve_provider(...)`
  - Prints “configuration is valid”
  - **Does not call** `provider::validate_provider`.
- `provider::validate_provider` already exists in `src/provider.rs`:
  - Checks mint/refresh/revoke command paths for existence/executable bits.
  - Returns `ProviderConfigError::ValidationFailed { problems }` with actionable strings.
- Error conversion exists (`From<ProviderConfigError> for Error`) in `src/error.rs`, so `ValidationFailed` will currently map to top-level `ErrorKind::Config`.
- Repo has extensive in-file test style; adding command wiring tests in `main.rs` is consistent with existing pattern.
- Important TDD issue discovered:
  - First newly added test already passed, indicating it asserted behavior already present (failure on missing provider command happens already through existing path), which violates the strict Red-phase requirement.
  - Need to rewrite Red tests so they fail against current implementation specifically because provider validation is not invoked by `cmd_validate`.

